1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:04,900
<i>You're paying me to work,
not to be spoken to like that!</i>

2
00:00:05,067 --> 00:00:06,433
<i> You're so harsh!</i>

3
00:00:06,567 --> 00:00:07,733
[SCREAMS]

4
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:11,200
<i>I really don't know why Martin
hired you as a secretary.</i>

5
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:12,967
<i>You're the
total opposite of him.</i>

6
00:00:13,100 --> 00:00:15,567
Well, opposites attract, right?

7
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:18,233
<i>- You're the hotel owners.
- Mm.</i>

8
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:21,567
<i>And he's a partner,
so you're on the same level.</i>

9
00:00:21,733 --> 00:00:23,933
<i> Handsome, rich,</i>

10
00:00:24,067 --> 00:00:26,233
<i> and business-minded!</i>

11
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,633
<i> You feel insecure?</i>

12
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:31,700
<i>This is him, and this is me.
There's a huge gap!</i>

13
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:34,200
<i>I think you should finish
what you started.</i>

14
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:37,600
<i> Don't leave her hanging.</i>

15
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:38,833
<i> Kiko, are you alright?</i>

16
00:00:38,967 --> 00:00:40,400
I just have so much work to do.

17
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:43,233
<i>I don't want
the new investor to think</i>

18
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,267
<i> that our workers are lazy.</i>

19
00:00:52,967 --> 00:00:59,833
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:02,333
[CLEARS THROAT] Miss Jade.

21
00:01:02,467 --> 00:01:05,600
Don't you think
you're staring a bit too much?

22
00:01:07,533 --> 00:01:08,500
Me?

23
00:01:09,133 --> 00:01:10,333
You?

24
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:12,833
Well, there's no one else here.

25
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:16,133
Come here. Let's have a talk.

26
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:18,367
- Ow...
- Sit here.

27
00:01:20,367 --> 00:01:27,367
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

28
00:01:42,033 --> 00:01:48,833
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

29
00:02:04,033 --> 00:02:10,833
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

30
00:02:20,433 --> 00:02:23,000
So, what's the deal
with you and Sir Kiko?

31
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:25,933
Why do people
keep asking me that?

32
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:27,167
Oh, do they?

33
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,500
Then, other people can see
what I've been seeing.

34
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:32,533
- What?
- That you're not just friends.

35
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,200
Raphie, we're just friends.

36
00:02:35,367 --> 00:02:37,533
That's not what I'm seeing.

37
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,400
I'm not sure
if I'm the only one,

38
00:02:39,533 --> 00:02:41,700
but from the moment
you came back here,

39
00:02:41,867 --> 00:02:44,167
he's always been
present in your life.

40
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:48,567
You were together
for the Roi incident.

41
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:50,867
[GASPS]

42
00:02:50,967 --> 00:02:51,967
<i> Kiko!</i>

43
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,100
<i> Jade?</i>

44
00:02:55,233 --> 00:02:57,233
<i>- Jade! Jade!
- [SOBBING]</i>

45
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,600
<i>- What's wrong?
- Kiko...</i>

46
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:04,700
And then,
during the team-building...

47
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,800
<i> Jade.</i>

48
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:09,700
<i>- I got it.
- No, it's okay.</i>

49
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,800
<i>- It's okay, I got it.
- It's fine...</i>

50
00:03:11,933 --> 00:03:14,033
<i>- Mudcart!
- Yes!</i>

51
00:03:14,133 --> 00:03:14,867
<i> I'll carry you.</i>

52
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,867
<i>- Kiko, I'm fine.
- Jade.</i>

53
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,300
<i> You're hurt. I'll carry you.</i>

54
00:03:18,433 --> 00:03:20,033
<i> Just go ahead.</i>

55
00:03:20,133 --> 00:03:21,800
<i>I'm not going
to leave you here.</i>

56
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:22,967
<i> Come on.</i>

57
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:25,800
[GRUNTS]

58
00:03:25,933 --> 00:03:26,800
[RAPHIE] And...

59
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,600
I think you were also together

60
00:03:29,767 --> 00:03:31,967
when you were gone
these past few days.

61
00:03:34,033 --> 00:03:40,900
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYS]

62
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:46,567
[RAPHIE] Am I right, Miss Jade?

63
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:48,800
[CHUCKLES]

64
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,167
Is that wrong?

65
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:52,233
Of course, not.

66
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:56,300
But it also isn't normal
for "just friends."

67
00:03:58,133 --> 00:04:00,033
You guys have something.

68
00:04:00,167 --> 00:04:01,200
I can feel it.

69
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:04,600
I can feel it in my fingers,
in my hair...

70
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:07,700
in your heart.

71
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,667
[TEASES]

72
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:12,800
In my... heart?

73
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:14,433
Yeah!

74
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:18,667
I don't know, but...

75
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:22,133
I feel like he's avoiding me
these past few days.

76
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:24,767
[JADE]
I don't know what I did wrong.

77
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:26,600
Have you asked him?

78
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:28,367
No.

79
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:30,467
It just doesn't make sense.

80
00:04:30,567 --> 00:04:35,300
Sometimes, he's so sweet
and kind to me.

81
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:38,800
I don't know
what his actions mean.

82
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:42,900
When something's confusing,
clear it up!

83
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:47,000
We don't have time
for mixed signals anymore.

84
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:49,900
Yeah.

85
00:04:50,033 --> 00:04:51,133
Yeah, you're right.

86
00:04:51,233 --> 00:04:53,300
- If it's confusing...
- Mm-hm.

87
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,067
- I should clear it up.
- Yes!

88
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,867
That's my girly pop.

89
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:00,467
So, if he can't say
what he really feels,

90
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,067
I'll say mine.

91
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:06,367
Perfect!

92
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:08,200
That's perfect!

93
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:10,167
Do that, Miss Jade!

94
00:05:10,267 --> 00:05:11,267
I'll root for you.

95
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,367
You're being too much.

96
00:05:12,533 --> 00:05:13,900
[CHUCKLES] Oh. Sorry.

97
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,500
That's the problem
when you're too bored.

98
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:20,433
You keep following me around.

99
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:25,333
Kiko, I just want an update
about you and Jade.

100
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:27,067
Come on.

101
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,600
Just help me with this,
will you?

102
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:32,200
- Here. Thank you.
- You know what?

103
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:34,200
You shouldn't
even be doing this.

104
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,067
This is your employees' job.

105
00:05:36,233 --> 00:05:38,467
You're the real bored one here.

106
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:41,133
So, what's up
with you and Jade?

107
00:05:43,233 --> 00:05:45,267
Hey, spill the tea!

108
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,600
I don't have to update you
about anything.

109
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:50,033
Jade and I are just friends.

110
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:52,300
[CHESKA SCOFFS] Friends?

111
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:55,233
You're such a prude.

112
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,733
Hey! Those are clean sheets!

113
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:02,367
I don't care.
I'll clean you up.

114
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,467
I'll clean your brain up.

115
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:07,300
The last time we talked,
you said, "soon."

116
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:09,233
You said you needed
a good timing.

117
00:06:09,367 --> 00:06:10,433
So, what now?

118
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:13,267
I realized I don't need it
anymore.

119
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:14,600
What?

120
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:17,967
[EXHALES] What does that mean?

121
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:22,767
Jade and I are just friends.

122
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:24,900
I only see her as a friend.

123
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:32,900
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS]

124
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,467
Alright, Pinocchio.

125
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,900
Why am I even your sister

126
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:44,100
if I don't know
how you really feel?

127
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,667
We're just so different.

128
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:49,267
She lives lavishly,
and I'm from the streets.

129
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:52,800
[SCOFFS] What is this, a drama?

130
00:06:52,967 --> 00:06:55,833
"We're worlds apart,
so we can't be together."

131
00:06:55,967 --> 00:06:56,667
My god.

132
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:59,667
I know she's not
that kind of person.

133
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,700
We just have
very different interests

134
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:05,267
and priorities in life.

135
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,867
Plus, Edward...

136
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,500
What? That she's more
compatible with Edward

137
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:12,933
because he's as rich as she is?

138
00:07:17,067 --> 00:07:20,633
When they're together,
it feels special.

139
00:07:22,267 --> 00:07:24,067
Special?

140
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:26,833
Why? Are they steamed buns?

141
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,633
Do they have a red dot
on their heads?

142
00:07:28,767 --> 00:07:30,467
What's so special about them?

143
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:34,333
All I'm saying is,
I can't compete with that.

144
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,800
How can I ever beat Edward?

145
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:38,067
- Just look at me.
- You look dirty!

146
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:42,300
I mean, those stuff look dirty.

147
00:07:42,433 --> 00:07:43,733
[CHUCKLES]

148
00:07:43,867 --> 00:07:47,900
I don't know if she noticed,
but I've been avoiding her.

149
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:49,700
What?!

150
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:51,367
Why did you do that?

151
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:53,500
- I'm crazy, I know.
- Yes, you are!

152
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,333
I know.
And I know it was wrong.

153
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:57,100
I shouldn't have done that.

154
00:07:58,367 --> 00:07:59,500
Well...

155
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:01,267
But you did do it.

156
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,500
You have to make it up to her.

157
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,667
Go talk to her.

158
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,667
And don't let your insecurities
get the best of you.

159
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,067
That's not right.

160
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:14,867
You can't just forget about
your feelings because of that.

161
00:08:15,033 --> 00:08:15,833
Come on, man.

162
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:19,367
I'm... I'm just
trying to be practical.

163
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:22,833
I don't want to push it too far
that it becomes awkward.

164
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:25,800
I'm fine with what we've got.

165
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:29,200
I'm just glad
to have her in my life again.

166
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:34,800
I don't want to ruin our
friendship with my feelings.

167
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:40,200
[SIGHS] Suit yourself.

168
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,567
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:48,767
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

170
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:53,067
[SOBBING, SNIFFLING]]

171
00:08:53,067 --> 00:08:54,700
Why are you crying, Jade?

172
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,967
Why are you hurting?

173
00:08:59,133 --> 00:09:00,667
There's nothing you can do,

174
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:02,833
Kiko only sees you as a friend!

175
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:04,067
See?

176
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,767
See?!

177
00:09:05,767 --> 00:09:07,533
It's because you keep
thinking about so many things.

178
00:09:07,533 --> 00:09:10,233
Turns out he only sees you
as a friend.

179
00:09:11,167 --> 00:09:12,733
It's all your fault!

180
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:15,833
It's all your fault
for expecting something!

181
00:09:18,133 --> 00:09:19,167
Jade?

182
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:24,100
[JADE CONTINUES SOBBING,
SNIFFLING]

183
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,767
Something wrong?

184
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:34,700
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

185
00:09:39,067 --> 00:09:40,600
[EDWARD GROANS]

186
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:43,667
Here.

187
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,167
What's that?

188
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:53,533
Just use my shoulder
to weep your tears with.

189
00:09:57,233 --> 00:09:58,467
Seriously?

190
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:00,933
Using your clothes?

191
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:03,033
Yeah well, I don't have
a handkerchief with me.

192
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:09,133
This shirt is pretty expensive,
you know?

193
00:10:09,933 --> 00:10:11,833
But I can always buy a new one.

194
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:18,733
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

195
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,767
[CHESKA] You're not even hiding

196
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,600
how you're waiting
for Justin anymore, huh?

197
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:39,900
Because I'm starting
to feel impatient.

198
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,667
I already want to start
the bar business.

199
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:44,867
I already made a business plan
and everything.

200
00:10:44,867 --> 00:10:46,667
The only thing missing
is the bar itself.

201
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:49,333
So you already made
a lot of progress, huh.

202
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,133
But not with apologizing,
I guess.

203
00:10:52,133 --> 00:10:54,367
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

204
00:10:54,367 --> 00:10:56,700
Alright. Let's say
that apologizing

205
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,567
wasn't really in your plan
in the first place.

206
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,600
Well, it already seems
so impossible.

207
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,300
It's not like you'll be
seeing him again, right?

208
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,333
He got suspended
by Luna after all.

209
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:08,733
You mean he's never
going back here at all?!

210
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:12,233
No way, Cheska!
I have to talk to him!

211
00:11:12,233 --> 00:11:14,333
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:16,700
What if we visit his house?

213
00:11:17,233 --> 00:11:18,700
You know where he lives?

214
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,133
Nope.

215
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:23,033
But we can ask Jade
and Luna, right?

216
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:25,567
We can.

217
00:11:25,767 --> 00:11:26,633
[CHESKA CHUCKLES]

218
00:11:26,633 --> 00:11:28,267
Won't he be shocked
with us suddenly

219
00:11:28,267 --> 00:11:29,800
showing up at his doorstep?

220
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,333
What if...

221
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:32,767
you give him a call first?

222
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:34,800
Alright, go do it then.

223
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:36,633
The hell...

224
00:11:36,633 --> 00:11:38,100
My idea, my work.

225
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:45,933
[PHONE VIBRATING]

226
00:11:45,933 --> 00:11:48,367
Justin, my friend!

227
00:11:48,367 --> 00:11:49,933
- [JUSTIN]<i> Hello?
</i>- Yeah!

228
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,400
It's been a while since
you last visited the hotel!

229
00:11:53,933 --> 00:11:54,967
How's it going?

230
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:56,300
[JUSTIN]<i> I have some
</i> business to attend to.

231
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:58,967
Huh?

232
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:00,767
Well, that's new! You busy?

233
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:03,267
What?

234
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:05,933
Let's go get some drinks!

235
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:08,133
[JUSTIN]<i> Alright, alright.
</i> I'll send you a message.

236
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:11,267
Yeah, message me
the time and place.

237
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:13,767
Later then!

238
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:14,767
Alright.

239
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,667
Bye, my friend!

240
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:17,633
[JUSTIN] Bye-bye.

241
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,433
[PHONE BEEPS]

242
00:12:19,900 --> 00:12:22,033
All done. We'll meet him later.

243
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:24,067
[SIGHS] Okay.

244
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:28,600
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING, FADES]

245
00:12:32,733 --> 00:12:34,633
You okay now?

246
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:40,033
Are you really not
gonna tell me what happened?

247
00:12:40,033 --> 00:12:42,867
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY DARREN
ESPANTO PLAYING]

248
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:45,100
Okay, then. Let's consider this
as a coffee update.

249
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,367
It's nothing.

250
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:51,667
Just pay it no mind.

251
00:12:57,367 --> 00:12:59,200
I would like to use
my third wish right now.

252
00:13:01,167 --> 00:13:02,567
Is it another breakfast?

253
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:04,733
Because I'm telling you
right now,

254
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:06,067
if it's breakfast,
I won't be able to--

255
00:13:06,067 --> 00:13:07,733
I want you to be free.

256
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,367
So you're going
to run away with me.

257
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,000
What?

258
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:19,200
Let's run away.

259
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:22,233
Somewhere far away
so you won't have

260
00:13:22,267 --> 00:13:23,367
to worry about a thing.

261
00:13:26,067 --> 00:13:27,233
A vacation?

262
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:30,200
If that's what you want,

263
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,200
then yes,

264
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,867
a vacation.

265
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:36,933
To get rid
of that negative energy

266
00:13:36,933 --> 00:13:38,833
that's making you cry.

267
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,233
Hold up, you can't say no.

268
00:13:45,267 --> 00:13:47,233
I saved your life, remember?

269
00:13:57,167 --> 00:13:58,800
When are we leaving?

270
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:02,067
[EDWARD CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

271
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:03,967
[EDWARD GRUNTING]

272
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,400
Let's get going.

273
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:12,933
Let's go?

274
00:14:12,933 --> 00:14:19,867
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
CONTINUES PLAYING]

275
00:14:20,967 --> 00:14:22,400
[EDWARD GROANING]

276
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:36,333
[RAPHIE] I approved Room 201's
request for a late checkout

277
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:39,000
tomorrow because no one
is booked in that room

278
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,267
- however,
- Okay.

279
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:42,933
Room 206 asked
for an extension.

280
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:44,800
206?

281
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:46,967
Hmm.

282
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:49,800
[WATER SPLASHING]

283
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:50,933
Sir?

284
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:53,300
Looks like the guest
really took a liking to Sari!

285
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,333
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

286
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:57,367
Thank you, Raphie. You can now
go back to work.

287
00:14:57,367 --> 00:14:58,633
Okay, sir.

288
00:14:58,633 --> 00:15:01,200
- [GUEST] Just us two!
- [SARI LAUGHING] Sir!

289
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,000
[GUEST] There's no one here!
Come on!

290
00:15:03,033 --> 00:15:05,233
[SARI] Go ahead, sir!
I'm still working.

291
00:15:05,233 --> 00:15:07,033
[GUEST] It's so lonely here.
Just join me!

292
00:15:07,033 --> 00:15:09,033
[SARI LAUGHING]

293
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:10,167
Sir?

294
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:12,800
Sir!

295
00:15:15,867 --> 00:15:17,167
[SARI GROANS] Sir!

296
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:19,267
Are you seriously doing that
with our guest?

297
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:20,967
- Sir?!
- Don't sir me!

298
00:15:21,233 --> 00:15:23,000
[PUFFS] I saw everything!

299
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:25,700
The way you laugh,
the way you smile at him!

300
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:28,067
- Sir, I didn't mean to!
- "Didn't mean to!"

301
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:29,233
Really?

302
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,833
You expect me to believe that?

303
00:15:31,367 --> 00:15:32,900
Sari, it's so obvious to me

304
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:34,333
that you're flirting
with a guest!

305
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:38,367
[MARTIN SCOFFS] I don't care

306
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:41,033
if you're doing or if you're
like this outside

307
00:15:41,033 --> 00:15:43,367
but don't bring that behavior
inside the hotel.

308
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:46,400
Because our hotel
is not that kind of place.

309
00:15:47,233 --> 00:15:49,933
[SOBS] Aren't you too cruel?

310
00:15:49,933 --> 00:15:55,933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

311
00:15:55,933 --> 00:15:58,233
Calling me a prostitute
would've hurt less.

312
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:03,233
[SARI SOBBING]

313
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:05,200
Why do I even bother
asking you?

314
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:09,033
You should've talked to me
properly about it first

315
00:16:09,067 --> 00:16:10,400
before judging me.

316
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:17,333
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

317
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:30,867
Mmh. [THUDS]

318
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:32,933
It's a peace offering.

319
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:34,033
Sorry.

320
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:37,200
What's that, Trixie?

321
00:16:37,767 --> 00:16:39,233
What kind of apology is that?

322
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:41,767
I can really feel the sincerity
in your voice!

323
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:46,300
That apology is colder than
the drink you're about to have.

324
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:47,433
Fix it!

325
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:50,100
Cheska, an apology
is an apology.

326
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,367
What more do you want?

327
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,233
There you go again.

328
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,800
When you apologize,

329
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,967
you should show
that you're really sorry.

330
00:16:58,967 --> 00:17:01,167
It should be felt
in your voice.

331
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:02,233
Like this.

332
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,867
Watch, okay?

333
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:08,400
Justin, I'm sorry.

334
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,900
I really didn't mean
what I said.

335
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,067
Like that! You can do it!

336
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:15,500
Like that? Really?

337
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:18,000
You sound like you're trying
too hard.

338
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,033
Look at you.

339
00:17:19,033 --> 00:17:21,267
We're practicing,
and you're acting like that.

340
00:17:21,867 --> 00:17:24,267
You don't take me seriously,
and you keep contradicting me.

341
00:17:24,267 --> 00:17:26,100
- Come on!
- Alright, fine.

342
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:27,300
Cheska!

343
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:32,267
You didn't tell me you were
with someone.

344
00:17:33,133 --> 00:17:36,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:17:41,167 --> 00:17:42,467
What are you doing?

346
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:47,533
I'm blessing the house
so your silence goes away.

347
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:50,167
You've been quiet at me
for a while now.

348
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:54,000
I got scolded by Sir Martin.

349
00:17:54,633 --> 00:17:57,000
He said some things to me.

350
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,000
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:03,367
Are you sad because...

352
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,633
you got scolded, or because
of what he said to you?

353
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:08,333
All of it.

354
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,633
Even if I was wrong,

355
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:14,167
I don't think I deserved
to be spoken to like that,

356
00:18:14,167 --> 00:18:15,867
even if it came from
someone perfect.

357
00:18:15,867 --> 00:18:16,933
Stop.

358
00:18:18,067 --> 00:18:19,267
He's not perfect.

359
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:21,567
My granddaughter
is the only one

360
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:24,033
who's close to perfect.

361
00:18:24,033 --> 00:18:26,067
- [CHUCKLES]
- Grandpa, come on.

362
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,367
Oh, dear.

363
00:18:30,433 --> 00:18:33,500
Even if what he said
isn't true,

364
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:36,600
you're still sad because it
came from someone you like.

365
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,200
[SARI SIGHS]

366
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:40,467
- Grandpa?
- Hmm?

367
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:45,033
What if the universe's sign
is wrong?

368
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:48,200
What if I was the only one
who gave meaning to it,

369
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,467
that Sir Martin is really
my soulmate?

370
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:52,500
What if he's not?

371
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:58,067
Do you like him
because of the signs,

372
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,633
or because of who he is?

373
00:19:00,633 --> 00:19:06,667
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,267
[SARI SIGHS]

375
00:19:14,367 --> 00:19:19,167
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

376
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:23,400
Miss! Miss!

377
00:19:26,033 --> 00:19:27,400
I don't think she can hear me.

378
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:30,233
I'll just order some snacks.

379
00:19:30,267 --> 00:19:32,400
- Do you want to eat?
- I'll do it.

380
00:19:32,967 --> 00:19:34,300
I'll buy the snacks.

381
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:36,733
I'll get fries, nachos,
and sea bass.

382
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:38,600
Sea bass? As a snack?

383
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:40,633
Uh, yeah.

384
00:19:40,633 --> 00:19:43,100
Sea bass is hard to find,
though.

385
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,467
It might take a while.

386
00:19:45,433 --> 00:19:46,967
I'll leave you two here.

387
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:48,433
I've got this.

388
00:19:49,267 --> 00:19:50,367
You've got this.

389
00:19:50,967 --> 00:19:52,200
[AWKWARD GIGGLE]

390
00:19:56,433 --> 00:19:57,133
[TRIXIE CLEARS THROAT]

391
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,433
[EXHALES]

392
00:20:04,767 --> 00:20:07,067
I'm sorry I can't stay
any longer, Grandma.

393
00:20:07,167 --> 00:20:08,833
I need to get back
to the hotel

394
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,767
so I can help my brothers.

395
00:20:12,167 --> 00:20:16,633
Last month,
you were busy with a client.

396
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:19,800
Now, it's your brothers.

397
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:23,967
To be honest,
they can manage without me.

398
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:26,667
But I still want to help them.

399
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:29,567
I also have to take care
of something at the hotel.

400
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:35,800
Tell me the truth.

401
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,500
It has something to do
with Luna, doesn't it?

402
00:20:41,033 --> 00:20:42,267
I guess so.

403
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:44,167
I need to find out
what she was doing

404
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:45,867
while she was here in Manila.

405
00:20:46,033 --> 00:20:47,533
[SIGHS]

406
00:20:48,567 --> 00:20:50,133
Oh, okay.

407
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:53,600
If this is about
you and Luna, go ahead.

408
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:56,767
You're a brave kid.

409
00:20:56,867 --> 00:20:58,200
So...

410
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:00,333
Go face this.

411
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,000
Thank you, Grandma.

412
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:04,533
- Mm.
- Mwah!

413
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:07,633
Always take care, my dear.

414
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:08,700
Yes, Grandma.

415
00:21:10,033 --> 00:21:12,533
- Mm...
- I'll go ahead now.

416
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:17,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

417
00:21:17,867 --> 00:21:19,900
Our lawyers are already
drafting the agreement.

418
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:23,233
Good, good.

419
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:26,533
Michael's children
also agreed to partner with me.

420
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:30,200
I won't go into
the details, but yes...

421
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:31,700
they agreed.

422
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:35,233
Oh... [CHUCKLES]
That's really good.

423
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:37,700
You know, this is what
I really wanted. I just...

424
00:21:37,867 --> 00:21:40,067
I just didn't think
it would be this easy.

425
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:41,367
[LUNA CHUCKLES]

426
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:45,167
Here are our terms.

427
00:21:45,267 --> 00:21:47,033
Our lawyers have reviewed them.

428
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,500
Good.

429
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:55,600
I'll have our lawyer
review this, too.

430
00:21:55,767 --> 00:21:58,233
But if it were up to me,
I'd approve it right away.

431
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,567
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

432
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,367
Good.

433
00:22:01,467 --> 00:22:03,667
I'm very excited
to be working with you.

434
00:22:04,433 --> 00:22:05,700
Thank you.

435
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:11,000
[MARINA] Juan!

436
00:22:11,767 --> 00:22:12,700
Juan!

437
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:16,033
Ma'am?

438
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:17,467
Juan!

439
00:22:18,467 --> 00:22:19,767
I didn't realize it was you,
ma'am.

440
00:22:19,933 --> 00:22:21,933
I've been trying
to get your attention.

441
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:23,400
I have news about your father.

442
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:24,933
Really, ma'am?

443
00:22:25,067 --> 00:22:29,067
Someone spotted him
in the town of Dagat-Dagatan.

444
00:22:29,167 --> 00:22:31,267
Dagat-Dagatan?

445
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:33,533
He's never mentioned
that place to me.

446
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:37,100
But it's a credible lead.

447
00:22:37,233 --> 00:22:38,233
According to the report,

448
00:22:38,333 --> 00:22:39,400
your father
had a project there.

449
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:40,633
Is that so?

450
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,200
Can I get
the contact information

451
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,433
of the person
who reported that?

452
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:46,267
It's back at the station.

453
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:47,767
I'll just send it to you.

454
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:49,933
Okay, ma'am.
Thank you very much.

455
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:56,900
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

456
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:07,300
<i>You apologize
to the people you hurt</i>

457
00:23:07,467 --> 00:23:11,267
<i>because you're considerate
of their feelings.</i>

458
00:23:11,367 --> 00:23:12,267
<i> But here you are,</i>

459
00:23:12,367 --> 00:23:13,933
<i>apologizing
for selfish reasons.</i>

460
00:23:14,033 --> 00:23:15,400
<i>- Justin!
- Go away!</i>

461
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,733
<i> Go back to the hotel.</i>

462
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:17,633
<i> Justin!</i>

463
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:19,600
<i> Wait a minute, Justin!</i>

464
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:22,333
<i>Do you know
Peter Montevilla?</i>

465
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:24,867
<i>He's madly in love
with Solenn.</i>

466
00:23:25,033 --> 00:23:28,133
<i>The map that leads to the
treasure hidden in Hotel 88.</i>

467
00:23:28,233 --> 00:23:30,133
- [VASE SHATTERS]
- [SHOUTS]

